AGAINST the backdrop of an alleged attack on him by the Oluwo of Iwo, Oba Abdulrasheed Akanbi, on Friday, the Agbowu of Ogbaagba, Oba Dhirulai Akinropo, on Saturday, threatened to drag the traditional ruler to court over the issue. It is recalled that Oba Akanbi had allegedly attacked his counterpart, Oba Akinropo, during a peace meeting over land tussle which was held inside the office of the Assistant Inspector General of Police, Zone 11, Mr Bashir Makama. Oba Akinropo, who spoke through his lawyer, Mr Babajide Siyanbola, to Sunday Tribune, said the alleged assault he suffered in the hands of Oluwo would not just be treated with kid gloves. According to him, “we would, as a matter of fact, institute a legal action against the Oluwo of Iwo, Oba Akanbi, over this matter very soon. We will definitely take action by seeking redress in the court of law.” Bayelsa: How Oshiomhole, Omo-Agege, Sylva, others lost out… Senator Abbo seeks establishment of technical college of… We will get bullion van driver who killed man in Ondo… Four children buried alive, four-year-old, six others… Meanwhile, some traditional rulers from Osun West Senatorial District have called for the immediate suspension of Oluwo by the Osun State government over what they termed ‘unruly behaviour and uncouth conduct’ on his part. Speaking on behalf of the traditional rulers , the Olu of Ile Ogbo, Oba Habeed Adetoyese, said: “We implore the government to immediately suspend him (Oluwo) so that we can have peace in our domain. “We have called our subjects that there is no cause for violence, but he should be checked. Only the governor can caution him and if that is not done, he would destroy the entire region.” “The state governor, Mr Gboyega Oyetola, should take action on Oluwo matter. This is because he was threatening us (Obas) on Friday at the AIG office. We don’t want a situation whereby hoodlums would be chasing us with guns in our palaces. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fru